WEBVTT

00:00:07.300 --> 00:00:11.220
- It's cold again today.
- So cold.

00:00:11.220 --> 00:00:13.790
I hope it snows!

00:00:13.790 --> 00:00:15.960
Me, too!

00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:20.070
- Will it snow?
- I hope it does.

00:00:21.250 --> 00:00:23.630
Is Onee-chan back already?

00:00:23.630 --> 00:00:25.460
Onee-chan!

00:00:27.760 --> 00:00:30.360
[I have a deadline today. I'll be heading out.]

00:00:31.620 --> 00:00:33.890
Wait, before you go!

00:00:36.270 --> 00:00:39.660
I want to make a snowman.

00:00:48.400 --> 00:00:51.590
Please tell us where to send an ambulance.

00:00:51.590 --> 00:00:54.530
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:00:54.530 --> 00:00:58.680
Medical emergency. I can't stop feeling nauseous.

00:00:58.680 --> 00:01:01.030
Please tell us where to send an ambulance.

00:01:01.030 --> 00:01:03.760
I'm at the Onomae bus stop.

00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:06.790
"Onomae," understood. And were you departing Onomae or arriving there?

00:01:06.790 --> 00:01:10.820
I was heading toward Hotani Station.

00:01:11.420 --> 00:01:14.150
All right, I will send an ambulance your way.
[Dispatch]

00:01:14.150 --> 00:01:16.350
Can I get your name and age please?

00:01:16.350 --> 00:01:18.640
Kono Ryoko.

00:01:19.730 --> 00:01:21.870
I am 53.

00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:24.030
Thank you, Ma'am.

00:01:24.730 --> 00:01:29.020
Kono-san, do you feel any other symptoms aside from nausea?

00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:31.930
Like chills or a headache, for example.

00:01:31.930 --> 00:01:35.460
No, none of those. I just suddenly felt...

00:01:40.800 --> 00:01:43.060
Kono-san, are you all right?

00:01:43.940 --> 00:01:47.540
Ma'am? What happened?

00:01:47.540 --> 00:01:49.230
She might not be able to answer verbally.

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:52.450
Have her respond by tapping the phone.

00:01:52.450 --> 00:01:55.880
Kono-san, are you unable to speak?

00:01:55.880 --> 00:02:00.890
If yes, then please tap the phone once.

00:02:04.770 --> 00:02:06.840
You can't speak, right?

00:02:06.840 --> 00:02:10.860
Is there anyone around you who could speak to us in your stead?

00:02:10.860 --> 00:02:14.470
If yes, then please tap the phone.

00:02:18.070 --> 00:02:19.970
So you are alone.

00:02:19.970 --> 00:02:23.600
Ma'am, are you able to breathe?

00:02:25.710 --> 00:02:30.890
Do you feel pain or any other symptoms aside from the nausea?

00:02:34.160 --> 00:02:36.760
Just feeling nauseous?

00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:40.400
Understood.

00:02:40.400 --> 00:02:42.430
The ambulance is already headed your way.

00:02:42.430 --> 00:02:45.140
Please make sure you remain somewhere safe.

00:02:45.140 --> 00:02:49.550
I will keep this line open in case you feel anxious.

00:02:50.270 --> 00:02:55.820
[119 Emergency Call]

00:02:55.820 --> 00:03:00.160
[CALL 7]

00:03:00.160 --> 00:03:02.460
My elder sister has aphonia.

00:03:02.460 --> 00:03:03.460
Was it my fault?

00:03:03.460 --> 00:03:05.330
I wanted to assuage her guilt, even just a little.

00:03:05.330 --> 00:03:07.150
Requesting a search and rescue.

00:03:07.150 --> 00:03:11.280
An 11-year-old boy has been reported missing by his father.

00:03:11.280 --> 00:03:13.480
Onee-chan, is that you?

00:03:13.480 --> 00:03:17.850
If yes, then please tap the phone once.

00:03:21.890 --> 00:03:23.320
[Incident Report]

00:03:23.320 --> 00:03:25.970
Writing a report on that call from earlier?

00:03:25.970 --> 00:03:27.380
Yes.

00:03:27.380 --> 00:03:33.560
That woman ended up communicating with the paramedics via writing as well.

00:03:33.560 --> 00:03:37.780
What's that symptom called again? Not aphasia, but...

00:03:37.780 --> 00:03:39.560
Aphonia.

00:03:39.560 --> 00:03:44.570
A loss of voice usually caused by mental strain or trauma.

00:03:44.570 --> 00:03:48.130
Yes, that. You're really knowledgeable about it.

00:03:48.130 --> 00:03:50.860
To be honest, my elder sister has aphonia.

00:03:50.860 --> 00:03:53.840
- What?
- She's had it about five years now.

00:03:53.840 --> 00:03:59.310
She's healthy and well aside from her voice, though.

00:03:59.310 --> 00:04:01.120
Five years...

00:04:01.780 --> 00:04:04.620
Is that why you decided to work for the Fire Bureau?

00:04:05.660 --> 00:04:07.200
Was I mistaken?

00:04:07.200 --> 00:04:11.360
It was five years ago that you considered joining the Fire Bureau,

00:04:11.360 --> 00:04:14.830
so I assumed it might have been related to that.

00:04:14.830 --> 00:04:18.980
I decided to join the Fire Bureau for a different reason, but...

00:04:18.980 --> 00:04:20.920
I still remember the person who answered my call

00:04:20.920 --> 00:04:23.970
when our house caught on fire.

00:04:23.970 --> 00:04:29.810
I want to be there for someone in their time of need as well.

00:04:30.580 --> 00:04:32.620
You are right.

00:04:33.800 --> 00:04:36.120
It was after that conversation that she...

00:04:38.580 --> 00:04:40.120
It's nothing.

00:04:40.120 --> 00:04:43.030
Could I ask you a question?

00:04:43.030 --> 00:04:44.600
Sure, go ahead.

00:04:44.600 --> 00:04:48.190
What do we do for individuals who call us but can't speak?

00:04:48.190 --> 00:04:52.680
We're unable to get the information we need from them.

00:04:52.680 --> 00:04:54.980
Oh, right.

00:04:54.980 --> 00:04:59.300
- In cases like that...
- Uesugi-kun, they went over this in training.

00:04:59.300 --> 00:05:00.300
Did they?

00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:02.440
You probably weren't listening.

00:05:02.440 --> 00:05:04.280
It seemed you took our work lightly at the time.

00:05:04.280 --> 00:05:05.900
That's not...

00:05:05.900 --> 00:05:08.270
You can't refute it entirely, can you?

00:05:08.270 --> 00:05:10.650
No, sorry.

00:05:10.650 --> 00:05:14.510
I commend your honesty, so let's give you a refresher.

00:05:14.510 --> 00:05:17.580
Perfect timing, as we've just printed new PSA* flyers.
(*Public Service Announcement)

00:05:17.580 --> 00:05:19.870
Here you are.

00:05:20.760 --> 00:05:22.740
"Contacting 119 from the web"?
[NET119: Emergency Call System]

00:05:22.740 --> 00:05:27.720
This is a service for those who can't report to 119 verbally.

00:05:27.720 --> 00:05:31.220
If you access the designated website from a mobile phone,

00:05:31.220 --> 00:05:33.870
you can file a report with the tap of a button.
[Medical emergency]

00:05:33.870 --> 00:05:39.160
Once connected to the command center, you can report the situation in text.

00:05:39.160 --> 00:05:41.870
This site is also connected to GPS services,

00:05:41.870 --> 00:05:44.770
so we can quickly pinpoint their location as well.

00:05:44.770 --> 00:05:49.130
But this site is inaccessible without prior registration, correct?

00:05:49.130 --> 00:05:51.980
Unfortunately, yes.

00:05:51.980 --> 00:05:54.590
We recognize the site isn't well known to citizens,

00:05:54.590 --> 00:05:58.300
so if you know anyone who could benefit from it, please spread the word!

00:05:58.300 --> 00:05:59.980
Will do.

00:06:11.270 --> 00:06:12.530
Hey there.

00:06:12.530 --> 00:06:14.280
Hello there.

00:06:14.280 --> 00:06:17.790
- Sir, are you all right?
- Me? I'm fine.

00:06:58.020 --> 00:07:00.390
[NET119: Emergency Call System]

00:07:00.390 --> 00:07:03.560
[If you need help applying, let me know.]

00:07:04.250 --> 00:07:07.690
- It's about time to switch, Kasuhara-san.
- Right.

00:07:10.650 --> 00:07:14.450
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:07:16.030 --> 00:07:21.680
My 3-year-old younger sister hit her head, and she's bleeding.

00:07:21.680 --> 00:07:24.970
Do you know where I should send the ambulance?
[3, female, head bleeding]

00:07:27.670 --> 00:07:30.880
I... did it.

00:07:32.620 --> 00:07:38.040
I pushed my sister, and... she fell.

00:07:41.270 --> 00:07:43.980
Is that your sister I hear crying?

00:07:43.980 --> 00:07:46.280
Yes.

00:07:46.280 --> 00:07:50.660
I... I've had enough of standing in for my mother.

00:07:50.660 --> 00:07:53.760
All my middle school friends get to have fun.

00:07:53.760 --> 00:07:56.410
Why do I have to do this?

00:07:56.410 --> 00:07:58.280
Could I ask where you two are right now?

00:07:58.280 --> 00:08:00.630
I'm sorry! I'm sorry.

00:08:00.630 --> 00:08:02.960
- It's okay. Let's calm down a bit.
- I'm sorry...

00:08:02.960 --> 00:08:05.080
Can you take a deep breath for me?

00:08:05.080 --> 00:08:07.540
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:08:07.540 --> 00:08:11.770
There's a small girl here crying and bleeding from her head.

00:08:11.770 --> 00:08:15.140
I thought she might need an ambulance. Poor thing. She's crying so hard.

00:08:15.140 --> 00:08:17.100
Please tell us where to send the ambulance.

00:08:17.100 --> 00:08:20.870
It's a park next to the intersection at Mizono.

00:08:20.870 --> 00:08:23.440
Looks like it's called "Mizonoe Park."

00:08:23.440 --> 00:08:26.570
Mizonoe Park by the intersection at Mizono, correct?

00:08:26.570 --> 00:08:29.150
- Could this be... Yogo-san.
- What?

00:08:29.150 --> 00:08:33.500
Is your call coming from District 2 of Mizono, in Kanagawa Ward?

00:08:33.500 --> 00:08:35.740
Yes. From the call's location, it seems so.

00:08:35.740 --> 00:08:37.940
So your name is Nazuna-chan?

00:08:37.940 --> 00:08:40.360
And what's your sister's name?
[3, female, head bleeding]

00:08:40.360 --> 00:08:44.120
- "Hina-chan"? Got it.
- How old is this injured girl?

00:08:44.120 --> 00:08:46.590
About two or three?

00:08:46.590 --> 00:08:49.830
Sorry, I'm driving and can't get a good look.

00:08:49.830 --> 00:08:52.540
- There's also a middle school girl next to her.
- I knew it.

00:08:52.540 --> 00:08:56.650
That may be the girl calling Kaneshita-san right now.

00:08:56.650 --> 00:09:00.650
Sir, could you possibly go speak to this girl?

00:09:00.650 --> 00:09:01.930
No way!

00:09:01.930 --> 00:09:05.380
I'm driving, and the light's about to change. Can I leave it to you?

00:09:05.380 --> 00:09:07.570
May... May I ask one last question?

00:09:07.570 --> 00:09:10.430
- Yes.
- What color are the two girls wearing?

00:09:10.430 --> 00:09:13.820
The younger girl is wearing a pink jacket.

00:09:13.820 --> 00:09:17.530
The middle schooler is wearing black.
[Pink, Black]

00:09:17.530 --> 00:09:20.250
- Thank you.
- Sorry, the folks behind me are honking.

00:09:20.250 --> 00:09:23.650
- If I could leave the rest to you...
- Yes, thank you.

00:09:23.650 --> 00:09:27.350
The younger girl is wearing pink, and the older child is wearing black.

00:09:27.350 --> 00:09:31.660
Say, could you tell me what colors you two are wearing right now?

00:09:31.660 --> 00:09:35.320
I'm wearing black, and Hina is wearing pink.

00:09:35.320 --> 00:09:36.800
Got it, thanks.

00:09:36.800 --> 00:09:39.800
We can assume this is the same case, yes?

00:09:41.370 --> 00:09:45.000
Kaneshita-san, no need to ask their location anymore―

00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:48.110
Nazuna-chan, I'll ask one last time.

00:09:48.110 --> 00:09:51.160
Could you tell me where you are right now?

00:09:51.160 --> 00:09:52.930
What?

00:09:52.930 --> 00:09:56.140
You called us because you wanted to save your sister, right?

00:09:56.140 --> 00:09:57.460
Oh...

00:09:57.460 --> 00:10:02.880
That's why you called 119 first and not the police.

00:10:03.820 --> 00:10:05.510
Y-Yeah.

00:10:05.510 --> 00:10:09.990
Then I think you should be honest with yourself.

00:10:09.990 --> 00:10:13.490
You must be the one to tell us where you two are.

00:10:13.490 --> 00:10:17.210
Otherwise, we can't send the ambulance where it needs to go.

00:10:18.270 --> 00:10:20.520
Well...

00:10:20.520 --> 00:10:23.960
- I don't know the exact address.
- That's fine.

00:10:23.960 --> 00:10:25.960
But we're at Mizonoe Park.

00:10:25.960 --> 00:10:28.700
Mizonoe Park. Thanks.

00:10:28.700 --> 00:10:31.210
I'll send the ambulance right away.

00:10:53.510 --> 00:10:55.700
[If you need help applying, let me know.]

00:10:55.700 --> 00:10:57.840
[Read]

00:11:07.060 --> 00:11:09.830
[Kasuhara Konatsu]
[090-332-414]

00:11:25.860 --> 00:11:27.880
Kaneshita-san?

00:11:30.300 --> 00:11:33.040
- Morning, Sir.
- Oh, hey.

00:11:37.400 --> 00:11:41.610
Those kids from yesterday live with their father following his divorce.

00:11:41.610 --> 00:11:46.880
The elder sister often misses school to care for her younger sister.

00:11:47.770 --> 00:11:49.510
Were you "imagining"?

00:11:49.510 --> 00:11:51.970
Like I'd ever take a page out of your book, Kasuhara.

00:11:51.970 --> 00:11:55.600
I just happened to overhear the folks here talking about them.

00:11:56.770 --> 00:12:04.680
Sir, why did you insist on having that girl tell you her location?

00:12:04.680 --> 00:12:06.790
The color of their clothes wasn't enough

00:12:06.790 --> 00:12:10.230
to prove our calls were about the same case.

00:12:10.230 --> 00:12:13.740
Is that really all there was to it?

00:12:13.740 --> 00:12:15.560
Are you doubting me?

00:12:20.230 --> 00:12:24.170
It's because I wanted to assuage her guilt, even just a little.

00:12:25.900 --> 00:12:29.450
Sure, she may have impulsively hurt her sister.

00:12:29.450 --> 00:12:33.360
But that girl called with the intent to save her.

00:12:33.360 --> 00:12:36.560
She should be made aware of that.

00:12:38.380 --> 00:12:43.720
It's better than assuming you were powerless in the situation.

00:12:44.850 --> 00:12:49.990
Now, whether her younger sister actually forgives her is a different story, though.

00:12:53.550 --> 00:12:56.210
I'm sure they'll be okay.

00:12:58.150 --> 00:13:02.910
I have an elder sister myself, so I understand.

00:13:05.630 --> 00:13:08.110
They won't ever come to hate one another.

00:13:08.810 --> 00:13:10.790
No matter what.

00:13:18.190 --> 00:13:20.470
[Otolaryngology: The Ear, Nose, and Throat]

00:13:23.530 --> 00:13:25.850
What are you studying up for?

00:13:27.280 --> 00:13:28.680
Hello there.

00:13:28.680 --> 00:13:30.770
Hey.

00:13:30.770 --> 00:13:33.620
- What about you?
- Me?

00:13:33.620 --> 00:13:35.630
I'm reviewing for this.
[Paramedic Qualifications]

00:13:38.480 --> 00:13:42.490
I feel there are plenty of things I can do

00:13:42.490 --> 00:13:45.650
and challenges I haven't tried yet in this work.

00:13:45.650 --> 00:13:47.280
Such as qualifying as a paramedic?

00:13:47.280 --> 00:13:49.410
Yes. I thought I'd start there.

00:13:49.410 --> 00:13:55.150
Qualifications will help me get promoted up the corporate ladder as well.

00:13:55.150 --> 00:13:56.590
"Promoted"?

00:13:56.590 --> 00:13:59.070
I've always had high aspirations.

00:13:59.070 --> 00:14:00.400
I see.

00:14:00.400 --> 00:14:03.560
So why were you looking at medical books?

00:14:03.560 --> 00:14:06.950
I think you were looking at something for "Otolaryngology"?

00:14:06.950 --> 00:14:11.580
Well, you know... things.

00:14:15.420 --> 00:14:20.200
We'll need to finalize a treatment plan for you right away.

00:14:20.200 --> 00:14:24.550
Please make your decision by our next checkup.

00:14:43.100 --> 00:14:46.140
- This looks delicious!
- Let's dig in!

00:14:46.140 --> 00:14:47.480
Yuki, portion it out for us, will you?

00:14:47.480 --> 00:14:49.020
- Okay.
- Thanks.

00:14:49.020 --> 00:14:50.920
Thank you!

00:14:51.660 --> 00:14:54.610
Oh, gosh. It seems this thing finally broke.

00:14:54.610 --> 00:14:57.080
I suppose it was getting old.

00:14:57.080 --> 00:14:59.630
Your next one should be a gas stove.

00:14:59.630 --> 00:15:00.920
What?

00:15:00.920 --> 00:15:04.870
I mean, it'd be useful during blackouts too, right?

00:15:07.360 --> 00:15:09.450
I see.

00:15:09.450 --> 00:15:13.870
Yes, I suppose enough time has passed by now.

00:15:14.960 --> 00:15:16.030
From what?

00:15:16.030 --> 00:15:20.300
- That fire. You still remember it, right?
- I do.

00:15:20.300 --> 00:15:24.480
You and Konatsu were both young when it happened,

00:15:24.480 --> 00:15:27.990
so we assumed any flame would remind you of it.

00:15:27.990 --> 00:15:32.360
That's why we avoided things that visibly used fire.

00:15:32.360 --> 00:15:36.130
Which is also why we never had candles for your birthdays.

00:15:36.130 --> 00:15:38.150
So that's why.

00:15:38.150 --> 00:15:41.960
I suppose we parents were being a bit too cautious.

00:15:42.650 --> 00:15:47.240
Come to think of it, you two never pressed us about the fire either.

00:15:47.240 --> 00:15:51.810
Next thing we knew, you were saying you wanted to be a dispatcher.

00:15:51.810 --> 00:15:54.300
I suppose life always has its surprises.

00:15:55.270 --> 00:16:02.180
It seems we were quick to assume that fire scared you.

00:16:02.180 --> 00:16:07.410
You're right. I guess it wasn't just a scary memory for me.

00:16:07.410 --> 00:16:10.060
But to Onee-chan...

00:16:11.220 --> 00:16:13.280
maybe that's all it was.

00:16:13.280 --> 00:16:14.610
What?

00:16:14.610 --> 00:16:18.120
I think Onee-chan's aphonia was triggered

00:16:18.120 --> 00:16:21.250
because I made her recall that fire.

00:16:21.250 --> 00:16:23.050
[Aphonia]

00:16:23.050 --> 00:16:24.960
Actually, she stopped speaking

00:16:24.960 --> 00:16:29.140
only after I said I wanted to become a dispatcher.

00:16:29.140 --> 00:16:31.070
Doesn't that mean...

00:16:32.180 --> 00:16:36.540
it was... all my fault?

00:16:36.540 --> 00:16:41.140
That's probably why she's avoiding me, too.

00:16:41.140 --> 00:16:43.330
No, that's not...

00:16:46.760 --> 00:16:48.960
For now, how about we eat?

00:16:48.960 --> 00:16:53.010
A full belly will chase those negative thoughts right out.

00:16:53.010 --> 00:16:54.440
Right.

00:16:55.840 --> 00:16:58.060
Hey, Yuki.

00:16:58.060 --> 00:17:00.750
Konatsu is holding an exhibition here.

00:17:00.750 --> 00:17:03.940
If you're free tomorrow, why don't you stop by?

00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:05.280
[Solo Exhibition: Kasuhara Konatsu]

00:17:05.280 --> 00:17:09.020
- But...
- You suddenly visited today

00:17:09.020 --> 00:17:12.350
because you were worried about her, right?

00:17:14.280 --> 00:17:15.890
Don't worry.

00:17:15.890 --> 00:17:20.990
No matter what the reason may be, Konatsu would never hate you.

00:17:41.990 --> 00:17:44.080
Thank you.

00:17:54.350 --> 00:17:57.790
I'm sorry I dropped by without warning.

00:17:57.790 --> 00:18:00.340
Mom told me about your exhibition.

00:18:04.630 --> 00:18:07.100
This is amazing, Onee-chan.

00:18:08.450 --> 00:18:10.800
Every piece looks beautiful.

00:18:17.630 --> 00:18:19.900
[Thank you.]

00:18:30.100 --> 00:18:32.620
I sent you a message about this,

00:18:32.620 --> 00:18:35.910
but I wanted to make sure you registered.

00:18:37.430 --> 00:18:40.300
Of course, you don't have to use this service.

00:18:40.300 --> 00:18:43.560
You can still call 119 in an emergency.

00:18:43.560 --> 00:18:49.610
Dispatchers know how to communicate with people who are unable to speak as well.

00:18:49.610 --> 00:18:55.820
I've even memorized your number so I'll know it's you at any time.

00:18:58.640 --> 00:19:00.420
Sorry.

00:19:00.420 --> 00:19:02.650
I guess that's a bit much, yes?

00:19:05.350 --> 00:19:12.130
Anyway, I promise I'll be there to help you, no matter what, Onee-chan.

00:19:13.390 --> 00:19:19.100
I don't know if that puts your mind at ease in the slightest.

00:19:19.100 --> 00:19:23.550
But if it's my fault for making you recall that fire,

00:19:23.550 --> 00:19:29.220
I just wanted you to know it'll be okay, and I'm here for you.

00:19:40.050 --> 00:19:43.160
[I never asked for your charity.]

00:20:04.530 --> 00:20:08.130
[Your company only hurts me.]

00:20:16.730 --> 00:20:19.390
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:20:19.390 --> 00:20:22.450
- Medical emergency.
- Where should I send the ambulance, Ma'am?

00:20:22.450 --> 00:20:25.440
In front of Mitsuba Bank's Yatsugawa branch.

00:20:25.440 --> 00:20:28.700
- "Mitsuba Bank's Yatsugawa branch"?
- Yes.

00:20:28.700 --> 00:20:30.260
May I ask what has happened and to whom?

00:20:30.260 --> 00:20:36.170
An elderly man is sitting in front of the bank, clutching his chest in pain.

00:20:36.170 --> 00:20:39.170
Is this individual conscious?

00:20:39.170 --> 00:20:43.380
Maybe? He seems to be a bit out of it.

00:20:43.380 --> 00:20:47.120
Please ask for his name and see if he responds.

00:20:47.120 --> 00:20:49.880
I see he's learning things well.

00:20:49.880 --> 00:20:51.320
True.

00:20:52.500 --> 00:20:56.050
Takachiho-san, don't you get bored up here?

00:20:56.050 --> 00:20:57.500
Why not sit down there for a change?

00:20:57.500 --> 00:20:59.120
What?

00:21:00.580 --> 00:21:03.110
You can leave command up here to me.

00:21:03.110 --> 00:21:05.190
I'll swap shifts with you.

00:21:05.190 --> 00:21:09.410
What are you saying? "The dispatcher up front is the star of the show."

00:21:09.410 --> 00:21:13.490
You often used to complain how boring it was up here, Sir.

00:21:13.490 --> 00:21:15.410
Did I now?

00:21:15.410 --> 00:21:18.160
Well, it was just an offer.

00:21:22.850 --> 00:21:25.500
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:30.300
Hi, does the fire department lend out any ladders?

00:21:30.300 --> 00:21:32.450
- "Ladders"?
- Yes.

00:21:32.450 --> 00:21:35.450
I lost my keys, and I'm locked out of my apartment.

00:21:35.450 --> 00:21:39.310
Since I'm on the second floor, I can enter from my balcony.

00:21:39.310 --> 00:21:42.660
Unfortunately, we do not accept such requests.

00:21:42.660 --> 00:21:45.230
I see. What do I do?

00:21:45.230 --> 00:21:48.460
Sorry, Sir. I'll be ending our call now.

00:21:51.790 --> 00:21:54.610
[Your company only hurts me.]

00:22:05.680 --> 00:22:07.750
How unusual.

00:22:10.020 --> 00:22:12.570
You didn't jog here today, did you?

00:22:14.110 --> 00:22:16.500
And that junk call about the ladder...

00:22:16.500 --> 00:22:21.630
Usually, you'd try to think of a solution with the caller.

00:22:24.230 --> 00:22:26.450
I guess it's not my business to pry.

00:22:27.280 --> 00:22:29.780
But your attitude's a bit off-putting today.

00:22:32.860 --> 00:22:34.630
Well...

00:22:36.090 --> 00:22:42.100
A while back, I told you how a dispatcher once saved my life.

00:22:42.100 --> 00:22:44.070
Do you remember?

00:22:44.070 --> 00:22:45.160
Yes.

00:22:45.160 --> 00:22:49.740
It happened when I was very young.

00:22:49.740 --> 00:22:55.340
My sister and I were watching the house when it suddenly caught on fire.

00:23:02.020 --> 00:23:04.100
Onee-chan!

00:23:11.070 --> 00:23:14.720
[119]

00:23:14.720 --> 00:23:18.090
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:23:18.090 --> 00:23:20.080
Fire.

00:23:21.140 --> 00:23:23.420
Please save us.

00:23:23.420 --> 00:23:27.010
Got it. Where are you right now?

00:23:27.010 --> 00:23:28.590
Home.

00:23:28.590 --> 00:23:31.180
"Home"... Your house is on fire?

00:23:31.180 --> 00:23:33.230
Yeah. The curtains are burning.

00:23:33.230 --> 00:23:35.910
- Are your parents out?
- Yeah.

00:23:35.910 --> 00:23:37.840
Then let's get you outside.

00:23:37.840 --> 00:23:41.030
Stay close to the floor and don't inhale the smoke.

00:23:41.030 --> 00:23:45.640
- Cover your mouth with a...
- But my onee-chan is here, too.

00:23:45.640 --> 00:23:47.950
What is she doing?

00:23:47.950 --> 00:23:51.570
She's sitting down. She won't move.

00:23:51.570 --> 00:23:53.520
She won't move?

00:23:53.520 --> 00:23:57.100
Does she look like she's sleeping?

00:23:57.100 --> 00:23:58.880
No.

00:23:58.880 --> 00:24:01.510
She's staring at the fire.

00:24:01.510 --> 00:24:05.420
Then tell your onee-chan she has to leave, too.

00:24:05.420 --> 00:24:09.260
Onee-chan, let's leave!

00:24:09.910 --> 00:24:15.770
To me, calling 119 and being rescued

00:24:15.770 --> 00:24:19.330
was what inspired me to pursue this career in the first place.

00:24:21.260 --> 00:24:22.810
But...

00:24:23.840 --> 00:24:30.050
The incident was terrifying for my sister. If she hadn't forgotten it,

00:24:30.050 --> 00:24:32.770
she couldn't have borne it.

00:24:34.530 --> 00:24:37.550
Except, I forced her to recall it.

00:24:39.240 --> 00:24:41.330
That's why her voice...

00:24:43.480 --> 00:24:49.520
I thought becoming a dispatcher meant I could save many lives.

00:24:49.520 --> 00:24:55.500
But as a result, I ended up hurting my own family.

00:24:59.190 --> 00:25:04.240
My imagination was lacking after all.

00:25:10.500 --> 00:25:14.680
I'm sure fear isn't all she felt.

00:25:16.510 --> 00:25:20.840
That fire didn't just leave your sister terrified.

00:25:22.120 --> 00:25:24.890
I'm sure it also left her with regret.

00:25:26.690 --> 00:25:28.480
"Regret"?

00:25:29.180 --> 00:25:33.210
She endangered someone she was meant to protect.

00:25:33.210 --> 00:25:36.300
That's a regret I understand all too well.

00:25:37.290 --> 00:25:40.140
- Kaneshita-san?
- Stay back!

00:25:40.980 --> 00:25:42.340
Shiomi.

00:25:42.340 --> 00:25:44.580
Shiomi! Shiomi!

00:25:44.580 --> 00:25:46.610
Shiomi!

00:25:48.100 --> 00:25:50.850
Neither your sister nor I could do a thing.

00:25:55.150 --> 00:25:59.070
We dispatchers aren't the only ones who want to save people.

00:25:59.070 --> 00:26:03.140
Never pressure someone to believe they're helpless and always need rescuing.

00:26:10.820 --> 00:26:13.050
[Your company only hurts me.]

00:26:15.970 --> 00:26:22.390
[Sorry about the other day.]

00:26:22.390 --> 00:26:24.510
Konatsu-san.

00:26:24.510 --> 00:26:27.850
Thank you for accompanying me today.

00:26:27.850 --> 00:26:30.370
Were you able to find much inspiration?

00:26:32.620 --> 00:26:35.160
That's beautiful!

00:26:36.150 --> 00:26:37.720
[I didn't realize there was so much greenery in Yokohama.]

00:26:37.720 --> 00:26:38.980
Right?

00:26:38.980 --> 00:26:43.510
And I'm sure your illustrations will make my article all the more appealing.

00:26:46.530 --> 00:26:50.830
I'm going to head back to the office. What about you?

00:26:53.150 --> 00:26:54.970
[I'm going to walk a bit farther along.]

00:26:54.970 --> 00:26:56.920
Got it.

00:26:58.830 --> 00:27:01.560
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:27:01.560 --> 00:27:05.240
More like a rescue than a medical emergency.

00:27:05.240 --> 00:27:06.730
What seems to be the matter?

00:27:06.730 --> 00:27:09.240
I was installing all-terrain tires for winter

00:27:09.240 --> 00:27:11.470
when the jack collapsed.

00:27:11.470 --> 00:27:13.890
My leg is stuck under my car.

00:27:13.890 --> 00:27:15.900
And it's still stuck, yes?

00:27:15.900 --> 00:27:17.790
- Yes.
- Understood.

00:27:17.790 --> 00:27:20.660
Please tell us where to send the ambulance.

00:27:21.290 --> 00:27:22.680
[Receive call]

00:27:22.680 --> 00:27:25.160
Kaneshita from Yokohama Fire Bureau Command speaking.

00:27:25.160 --> 00:27:29.200
This is Mukai from 110 requesting a search and rescue.

00:27:29.200 --> 00:27:31.490
An 11-year-old boy has been reported missing by his father

00:27:31.490 --> 00:27:35.650
in Sasanodai Forest, Isogo Ward.

00:27:35.650 --> 00:27:38.510
Search for an 11-year-old boy. Copy that.
[Lost? 11, male]

00:27:38.510 --> 00:27:41.530
Where is the father currently?

00:27:41.530 --> 00:27:44.180
He called from Hinode Park, also located in Sasanodai Forest.
[Exclusive use]

00:27:44.180 --> 00:27:46.840
"Hinode Park." Understood.

00:27:46.840 --> 00:27:48.750
We'll send a rescue squad right away.

00:27:48.750 --> 00:27:50.250
It's all forest around there.
[Sasanodai Forest Area]

00:27:50.250 --> 00:27:52.310
I hope he didn't wander far.

00:27:52.310 --> 00:27:53.560
Could we get further details?

00:27:53.560 --> 00:27:58.950
Yes. The missing boy is named Sakurai Ryota-kun, who is 11 years old.

00:27:58.950 --> 00:28:02.020
He was hiking with his parents, but after arguing with his mother,
[Sakurai Ryota]

00:28:02.020 --> 00:28:06.000
he wandered ahead of both his parents on the hiking trail.

00:28:06.000 --> 00:28:08.750
When the parents arrived at Hinode Park, he couldn't be found.

00:28:08.750 --> 00:28:12.930
They searched the area for an hour to no avail.

00:28:12.930 --> 00:28:16.030
- Have you asked them what Ryota-kun wore today?
- Yes.

00:28:16.030 --> 00:28:20.470
He was wearing a brown jacket, navy pants, and an orange backpack.

00:28:20.470 --> 00:28:24.490
- Copy that.
- We've told the family you may need to hear from them.

00:28:24.490 --> 00:28:26.440
May I give you their number?
[Backpack, Orange]

00:28:26.440 --> 00:28:28.640
Please do.

00:28:32.100 --> 00:28:35.570
- This is Yokohama Fire Bureau.
- This is Captain Iida of Central Rescue Squad.

00:28:35.570 --> 00:28:38.330
We've searched within an 800-meter radius around Hinode Park

00:28:38.330 --> 00:28:40.350
but haven't found the boy.

00:28:40.350 --> 00:28:43.100
Requesting back-up to aid with the search.

00:28:43.100 --> 00:28:46.080
We'll send in another firefighting team and a paramedic team.

00:28:46.080 --> 00:28:49.370
We have only an hour until sunset.

00:28:51.600 --> 00:28:55.410
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:28:58.540 --> 00:29:02.120
Hello? Can you hear me?

00:29:04.900 --> 00:29:10.150
Are you perhaps unable to speak now?

00:29:10.150 --> 00:29:15.070
If yes, please tap the phone once.

00:29:19.700 --> 00:29:21.680
You can't speak. Understood.

00:29:21.680 --> 00:29:23.840
In that case...

00:29:25.050 --> 00:29:28.140
[Phone number: 090-332-414]

00:29:28.140 --> 00:29:29.410
What?

00:29:29.410 --> 00:29:32.500
I've even memorized your number
[Kasuhara Konatsu: 090-332-414]

00:29:32.500 --> 00:29:35.240
so I'll know it's you at any time.
[Phone number: 090-332-414]

00:29:36.020 --> 00:29:39.240
Onee-chan, is that you?

00:29:41.470 --> 00:29:45.920
If yes, then please tap the phone once.

00:29:50.560 --> 00:29:52.460
Onee-chan...

00:29:55.090 --> 00:29:57.180
This is no time to be surprised.

00:29:58.060 --> 00:30:02.870
If it's a fire, tap the phone once. Three times if it's a medical emergency.

00:30:06.390 --> 00:30:08.300
She needs an ambulance...

00:30:08.300 --> 00:30:11.540
I'm going to ask you several questions now.

00:30:11.540 --> 00:30:14.320
Tap once for yes, okay?

00:30:15.210 --> 00:30:18.710
Are you the one who needs an ambulance?

00:30:21.970 --> 00:30:23.840
It's someone else?

00:30:26.040 --> 00:30:28.510
Is this person conscious?

00:30:30.380 --> 00:30:32.740
Are they breathing?

00:30:34.610 --> 00:30:37.040
So they're breathing and conscious.

00:30:38.180 --> 00:30:40.410
Are they hurt?

00:30:42.760 --> 00:30:44.760
Are they bleeding?

00:30:47.410 --> 00:30:49.280
They're not bleeding?

00:30:50.130 --> 00:30:53.110
Which means it's possibly a sprain or broken bone.

00:30:53.970 --> 00:30:57.720
Now, I'll ask about where you are.

00:30:57.720 --> 00:31:01.750
Onee-chan, are you around Mt. Okamine?

00:31:02.970 --> 00:31:05.500
Were you in the middle of a hike?

00:31:08.510 --> 00:31:10.830
Okay.

00:31:10.830 --> 00:31:14.010
Do you know where you are along the trail?

00:31:14.010 --> 00:31:16.640
She has her location turned off.

00:31:20.040 --> 00:31:22.070
She doesn't know.

00:31:22.070 --> 00:31:25.200
Kasuhara, send her a link to "Video 119."

00:31:25.200 --> 00:31:28.890
That'll turn her GPS on, and we'll get more information from a video.

00:31:28.890 --> 00:31:30.120
Yes, Sir.

00:31:30.120 --> 00:31:33.750
Onee-chan, I'm going to send you a URL.

00:31:33.750 --> 00:31:37.180
Accessing it will connect us to your phone's camera.

00:31:37.180 --> 00:31:39.670
If that works for you, could I get a response?

00:31:43.480 --> 00:31:45.490
I just sent it.

00:31:45.490 --> 00:31:49.340
Follow the instructions on the page once you click the URL, okay?

00:31:49.340 --> 00:31:51.810
I'll end this call and be ready to switch over.

00:31:54.100 --> 00:31:57.410
Does your sister have pen and paper on hand?

00:31:57.410 --> 00:31:59.390
I think she does.

00:31:59.390 --> 00:32:02.610
Then she can communicate by writing over video.

00:32:02.610 --> 00:32:04.360
You're right.

00:32:05.130 --> 00:32:06.300
[Connecting]

00:32:07.290 --> 00:32:08.640
[Report Information]

00:32:08.640 --> 00:32:10.240
Onee-chan, we see you.

00:32:10.240 --> 00:32:13.510
We were able to narrow down your location; we'll send a squad your way.

00:32:13.510 --> 00:32:17.100
She's quite far off the trail.

00:32:17.100 --> 00:32:19.860
- I'm calling a chopper, too.
- Please do.

00:32:24.330 --> 00:32:28.280
Onee-chan, can you show us who is hurt?

00:32:34.440 --> 00:32:35.630
Isn't that...

00:32:35.630 --> 00:32:40.120
Brown jacket, navy pants, and an orange backpack?

00:32:40.120 --> 00:32:42.160
It's the lost boy.

00:32:42.160 --> 00:32:46.160
I see now. Mt. Okamine is connected to Sasanodai Forest.

00:32:46.160 --> 00:32:50.180
Should I contact the squads currently searching for the boy?

00:32:50.180 --> 00:32:53.570
Kasuhara-san, could you ask her for the boy's name just in case?

00:32:53.570 --> 00:32:55.110
Yes, Ma'am.

00:32:55.110 --> 00:32:59.140
Onee-chan, can you ask that boy for his name?

00:33:10.590 --> 00:33:12.130
[What's your name?]

00:33:16.460 --> 00:33:18.380
[Sakurai Ryota]

00:33:18.380 --> 00:33:19.940
Sakurai Ryota-kun? Got it.

00:33:19.940 --> 00:33:23.440
To all squads currently searching in Sasanodai Forest:
[Sakurai Ryota]

00:33:23.440 --> 00:33:25.740
the missing 11-year-old boy is with a woman

00:33:25.740 --> 00:33:29.060
who has called for help from Mt. Okamine.

00:33:29.060 --> 00:33:31.160
I will call with further details, over.

00:33:31.160 --> 00:33:32.960
Copy that.

00:33:32.960 --> 00:33:36.800
The squad we sent out from Sakae

00:33:36.800 --> 00:33:39.350
is still 2 kilometers from Mt. Okamine.

00:33:39.350 --> 00:33:42.240
Your squad from Central might reach them first.

00:33:43.090 --> 00:33:45.980
I wonder if he slipped and hurt his leg.

00:33:45.980 --> 00:33:48.620
Onee-chan, you're not hurt, are you?

00:33:50.630 --> 00:33:53.460
Kasuhara, get her to show us the boy's face.

00:33:53.460 --> 00:33:54.810
Yes, Sir.

00:33:54.810 --> 00:33:58.660
Onee-chan, could you show us Ryota-kun's face?

00:34:05.030 --> 00:34:06.540
This is...

00:34:06.540 --> 00:34:09.170
He's showing the first signs of hypothermia.

00:34:09.170 --> 00:34:12.330
If his body temperature gets any lower, worst-case scenario...

00:34:12.330 --> 00:34:14.960
His heart could stop.

00:34:17.520 --> 00:34:21.510
Onee-chan? Hello? Are you there?

00:34:25.390 --> 00:34:27.360
[What should I do to help?]

00:34:33.880 --> 00:34:36.610
[I want to help save this boy.]

00:34:37.760 --> 00:34:41.290
Okay. Let's save him together.

00:34:41.290 --> 00:34:44.190
We can't let his temperature get any lower than it already is.

00:34:44.190 --> 00:34:49.200
If you have any jackets he could wear, bundle him up.
[Symptoms of hypothermia]

00:34:49.200 --> 00:34:52.600
A picnic blanket would also do the trick.

00:34:52.600 --> 00:34:56.750
Share any warm drinks you might have as well.

00:34:59.030 --> 00:35:01.950
And if you have any hand warmers,

00:35:01.950 --> 00:35:05.760
place them on his neck, ankle, and armpits.
[Initial Response]

00:35:05.760 --> 00:35:08.570
Rescue squads, this is Yokohama Fire Bureau.

00:35:08.570 --> 00:35:12.570
The 11-year-old boy is beginning to suffer from hypothermia.

00:35:12.570 --> 00:35:14.830
We are currently attempting to keep him warm.

00:35:14.830 --> 00:35:16.950
This is Central. Copy that.

00:35:16.950 --> 00:35:18.830
We are 400 meters from their location.

00:35:18.830 --> 00:35:20.090
This is Yokohama Fire Bureau. Copy that.

00:35:20.090 --> 00:35:22.490
- Keep moving!
- Yes, Sir!

00:35:24.550 --> 00:35:25.910
They're almost there.

00:35:25.910 --> 00:35:28.650
The rescue squad is about 15 minutes out.

00:35:33.930 --> 00:35:35.420
Are we getting interference?

00:35:35.420 --> 00:35:36.950
Hopefully that didn't mess with her GPS.

00:35:36.950 --> 00:35:38.710
I'm worried about the weather as well.

00:35:38.710 --> 00:35:40.590
Rain clouds are approaching their location.

00:35:40.590 --> 00:35:43.340
I suspect rain in the next 20 minutes or so.

00:35:43.340 --> 00:35:46.900
Onee-chan, it might start raining soon.

00:35:46.900 --> 00:35:52.380
Try to move him somewhere he can be dry and out of the rain.

00:36:17.730 --> 00:36:19.910
[Ryota-kun looks drowsy.]

00:36:21.720 --> 00:36:24.310
His hypothermia is getting worse.

00:36:24.910 --> 00:36:26.750
[Ryota-kun looks drowsy.]

00:36:31.630 --> 00:36:34.020
Kasuhara-san, shaking him is more dangerous.

00:36:34.020 --> 00:36:36.020
Tell her to let him lie down.

00:36:36.020 --> 00:36:38.650
Onee-chan, don't force him to wake up.

00:36:38.650 --> 00:36:41.330
Have him lie down as is.

00:36:43.330 --> 00:36:45.210
He'll be okay.

00:36:45.960 --> 00:36:47.800
The rescue team will arrive soon.

00:36:47.800 --> 00:36:51.050
- And the rain?
- Could start any minute now.

00:36:53.460 --> 00:36:56.750
- Yokohama Fire Bureau.
- Yokohama Fire Bureau, this is Central.

00:36:56.750 --> 00:36:58.920
We've arrived at the designated location,

00:36:58.920 --> 00:37:03.240
but we see no individuals within a 50-meter radius.

00:37:03.240 --> 00:37:05.510
Their GPS signals are getting messed up.

00:37:05.510 --> 00:37:08.030
We will expand our radius and continue our search.

00:37:08.030 --> 00:37:11.760
Both individuals needing rescue cannot speak, correct?

00:37:11.760 --> 00:37:13.330
Yes.

00:37:20.080 --> 00:37:21.760
Kasuhara-san!

00:37:21.760 --> 00:37:25.180
- Yokohama Fire Bureau!
- Anyone there?

00:37:28.380 --> 00:37:30.850
Yokohama Fire Bureau!

00:37:30.850 --> 00:37:33.080
Ryota-kun!

00:37:33.080 --> 00:37:34.650
Kasuhara-san!

00:37:34.650 --> 00:37:36.140
Sakurai Ryota-kun!

00:37:36.140 --> 00:37:38.470
Is anyone there?

00:37:40.000 --> 00:37:42.360
Kasuhara-san!

00:37:50.190 --> 00:37:51.850
Rain?

00:38:12.400 --> 00:38:14.210
Onee-chan?

00:38:18.210 --> 00:38:20.860
She's trying to climb up.

00:38:51.610 --> 00:38:54.250
Onee-chan, are you okay? Hello?

00:38:54.250 --> 00:38:55.560
Can you hear me?

00:38:55.560 --> 00:38:57.570
Onee-chan?

00:38:58.360 --> 00:39:00.400
Onee-chan?

00:39:06.070 --> 00:39:09.620
Is anyone there? We've come to help!

00:39:09.620 --> 00:39:13.550
Please make any sort of noise if you're there!

00:39:13.550 --> 00:39:15.270
We've come to help!

00:39:15.270 --> 00:39:17.310
Is anyone there?

00:39:17.310 --> 00:39:18.470
Kasuhara-san!

00:39:18.470 --> 00:39:20.320
They're right here!

00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:24.360
- Both individuals needing rescue are right here!
- Kasuhara Konatsu-san!

00:39:24.360 --> 00:39:26.920
Sakurai Ryota-san!

00:39:36.780 --> 00:39:39.350
They're right here!

00:39:49.940 --> 00:39:53.050
Kasuhara Konatsu-san!

00:39:58.480 --> 00:40:01.650
Both individuals in need of rescue are right here!

00:40:11.340 --> 00:40:17.020
I promise I'll be there to help you, no matter what.

00:40:17.020 --> 00:40:21.290
I just wanted you to know it'll be okay, and I'm here for you.

00:40:21.290 --> 00:40:24.740
Onee-chan, let's leave!

